{"word":"θάομαι","slug":"θάομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θάομαι</b></el> <el>(θάομαι,) </el><p/><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to wonder at, admire</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>later, <i>to gaze on, see</i>, 2nd <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>θᾶσθε</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <a href='S:imperative mood'>imperat.</a> <el>θάεο</el> <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>: doric <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>θασόμενος</el> <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>; aor1 <a href='S:imperative mood'>imperat.</a> <el>θᾶσαι</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>θάσασθαι</el> <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}